Gemini said

*The QR FIFO Flow Just Got Simpler!*



We are excited to roll out the revamped *QR FIFO Flow*, designed to
drastically cut down the time and effort riders spend picking up a package.


By eliminating redundant steps, this update ensures a smoother, more
intuitive, and error-free on-ground operations experience.


Why We Built This?









Our goal is always to make the rider=E2=80=99s journey as smooth and effici=
ent as
possible. By analyzing field data and direct rider feedback, we've unlocked
new ways to simplify daily operations and save valuable time on the ground.


This update is all about maximizing efficiency, replacing multi-step
confirmation sequences with lightning-fast transitions and introducing
instant, clear scanning feedback. We built this to remove unnecessary
steps, minimize clicks, and give riders a more intuitive, stress-free tool
to power through their day.
What=E2=80=99s New!



   1.

   *Streamlined Multi-Screen Workflow:* We have completely eliminated the
   "Accept Modal" and intermediate pickup screens in the QR FIFO Flow.
Swiping *Complete
   Pickup* now would lead riders directly onto the *Start for Drop* screen.


   2.

   *Frictionless Manual Entry:* If a QR code is damaged and can't be
   scanned within 3 seconds, a button asking the rider to =E2=80=98enter de=
tails
   manually=E2=80=99 will appear. After clicking, another screen will pop u=
p to let
   the rider manually enter the order ID. The rider can also scan the packa=
ge
   again, if need be.


   3.

   *Classified Scan Errors:* No more generic "Order not found" messages.
   Riders will now see precise error states for *Already Picked Up*, *Order
   Cancelled*, or *Connection Issues* with a clear call-to-action to try
   again.


What This Means To You





Every second counts in dense, high-volume delivery environments. By
trimming the excess clicks from the pickup journey, riders can load up and
get moving much faster, directly translating to *higher productivity and
better earnings per hour*.


*And this also works in the batching flow where riders can scan upto 3
orders in the QR FIFO journey.*
What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned !!
